theorem dense_P1_implies_dense_interior {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense A → Topology.P1 A → Dense (interior A) := by
  intro hDense hP1
  -- We show that `closure (interior A)` is the whole space.
  have h_closure_int : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    -- First, `closure A` is the whole space by density of `A`.
    have h_closureA : closure A = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
      simpa using hDense.closure_eq
    -- From `P1`, we have `A ⊆ closure (interior A)`, hence
    -- `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`.
    have h_sub : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
      have h_sub' : A ⊆ closure (interior A) := hP1
      have : closure A ⊆ closure (closure (interior A)) :=
        closure_mono h_sub'
      simpa using this
    -- Combining these facts we obtain the desired equality.
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro x _; exact Set.mem_univ x
    · simpa [h_closureA] using h_sub
  -- Reformulate the equality as a `Dense` statement.
  simpa [Dense] using h_closure_int

theorem interior_closure_interior_closure_interior_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (interior A)))) =
      interior (closure (interior A)) := by
  simpa using
    (Topology.interior_closure_interior_closure_eq (X := X) (A := interior A))
